00:00:01.100 --> 00:00:05.670
I'm really excited for you to get to the project phase of this course.

00:00:05.670 --> 00:00:08.940
You're going to learn an immense amount in a short period of

00:00:08.940 --> 00:00:13.665
time and you're going to get to prove your mastery in all of it at once,

00:00:13.665 --> 00:00:15.525
in one cohesive project.

00:00:15.525 --> 00:00:19.125
Here's the scene, you've been hired by UdaPeople,

00:00:19.125 --> 00:00:23.460
an innovative company with a revolutionary concept in human resources,

00:00:23.460 --> 00:00:26.430
which promises to help small businesses care

00:00:26.430 --> 00:00:30.210
better for their most valuable resource, their people.

00:00:30.210 --> 00:00:32.700
The success of their product depends on

00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:36.900
quick releases in a rock solid, high-quality product.

00:00:36.900 --> 00:00:40.850
In this course, I'm going to teach you the skills that you need to make sure

00:00:40.850 --> 00:00:46.195
UdaPeople has the chance to release their innovative product to the world market.

00:00:46.195 --> 00:00:48.035
By the end of this course,

00:00:48.035 --> 00:00:51.350
you'll be able to explain the fundamentals and benefits of

00:00:51.350 --> 00:00:56.950
CICD to achieve build and deploy automation for Cloud-based software products.

00:00:56.950 --> 00:01:00.980
You'll be able to utilize deployment strategies to design and

00:01:00.980 --> 00:01:05.465
build CICD pipelines that support continuous delivery processes.

00:01:05.465 --> 00:01:08.420
You'll utilize a configuration management tool

00:01:08.420 --> 00:01:11.740
to accomplish deployment to Cloud-based servers,

00:01:11.740 --> 00:01:14.960
and you'll surface critical errors for diagnosis using

00:01:14.960 --> 00:01:19.380
centralized structured logging and much more.

